[---  
description: >
Enforce strict coding and commit conventions for all changes, including Git commit formatting, visual consistency using @remixicon/react, and matching new page designs to the landing page.

globs:

- "\*_/_.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,json,md,css,scss,html}"

alwaysApply: false
---]

rules:

# ✅ Git Commit Rules

- id: git-conventional-commits
  description: >
  All commits must follow the Conventional Commits format with Gitmoji. Messages must be concise, lowercase, and end with a period.
  condition: >
  commit.message matches /^(🔧|✨|🐛|💄|⚡️|🎨|✅|🚧|📝|💥) (feat|fix|style|refactor|perf|chore|test|docs|wip)(\([\w\-]+\))?!?: .+\.$/
  errorMessage: >
  ❌ Commit message must follow Conventional Commits + Gitmoji:
  "<emoji> <type>(optional-scope): message." (ends with a period).

# ✅ Git Commit Scope Guidelines

- id: git-scope-format
  description: >
  If a scope is used, it must be lowercase and contain only letters, numbers, or dashes.
  condition: >
  !commit.message.contains("()") && (commit.message contains "(" && commit.message contains ")")
  action: >
  ensure commit.message.scope matches /^[a-z0-9\-]+$/
  errorMessage: >
  ❌ Scope in commit message must be lowercase and use dashes only.

# ✅ Enforce use of @remixicon/react

- id: remixicon-import
  description: >
  All icons must be imported from '@remixicon/react'.
  condition: >
  file.content.includes("Icon") && !file.content.includes("@remixicon/react")
  errorMessage: >
  ❌ All icons must be imported from '@remixicon/react'.

# ✅ Consistent Page Design with Landing Page

- id: consistent-design
  description: >
  All new pages must match the landing page design system and color scheme.
  condition: >
  file.path.includes("/pages/") && file.diff.added.includes("<div") && !file.diff.added.includes("className=\"landing-style\"")
  errorMessage: >
  ❌ New pages must follow the same layout, spacing, and colour scheme as the Landing Page. Reuse design components.

# ✅ Prevent vague commits

- id: no-vague-commit
  description: >
  Avoid vague commit messages like "update", "fix stuff", or "misc changes".
  condition: >
  commit.message matches /update|fix(stuff)?|misc/
  errorMessage: >
  ❌ Commit messages must be specific and meaningful. Avoid vague words like "update" or "fix stuff".

# ✅ Force short commit messages

- id: concise-commit
  description: >
  Keep commit messages short (max 72 characters).
  condition: >
  commit.message.length > 72
  errorMessage: >
  ❌ Commit message too long. Keep it under 72 characters.
